    • Field Detail

      • OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED

        static final String OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED
        A save option that can be used only with save(Map) to specify that the model is to be saved only if the new contents are different from actual contents; this compares the bytes in the backing store against the new bytes that would be saved. The value on this option can be either null, OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_FILE_BUFFER, or OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_MEMORY_BUFFER.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_MEMORY_BUFFER

        static final String OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_MEMORY_BUFFER
        A value for OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED to specify that an in-memory buffer should be used to compare the new contents with the actual contents. This will be faster than OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_FILE_BUFFER but will use up more memory.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_FILE_BUFFER

        static final String OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_FILE_BUFFER
        A value for OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED to specify that a file buffer should be used to compare the new contents with the actual contents. This will be slower than OPTION_SAVE_ONLY_IF_CHANGED_MEMORY_BUFFER but will use up less memory.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • OPTION_CONTENT_DESCRIPTION

        static final String OPTION_CONTENT_DESCRIPTION

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

        static final String OPTION_MIME_TYPE

      • delete

        void delete(Map<?,?> options)
     throws IOException
        deletes the model resource using the specified options, unloads it, and then removes it from the containing model set.

        Options are handled generically as feature-to-setting entries; the model will ignore options it doesn't recognize. The options could even include things like an Eclipse progress monitor...

        An implementation typically uses the URI converter of the containing resource set to IURIConverter.delete(URI, Map) the ontology's URI.

        Throws:
        IOException

        IModelSet getModelSet()
        Returns the containing model set. A model is contained by a model set if it appears in the models, i.e., the contents, of that model set. This reference can only be modified by altering the contents of the model set directly.

      • getURI

        URI getURI()
        Returns the URI of this model. The URI is normally expected to be absolute and hierarchical; document-relative references will not be serialized and will not be resolved, if this is not the case.
        Returns:
        the URI of this model, or null if there isn't one.
        See Also:

        Returns whether the model is loaded.

        This will be false when the model is first created and will be set to false, when the model is unloaded. It will be set to true when the model is loaded.

      • load

        void load(Map<?,?> options)
   throws IOException
        Loads the model using the specified options.

        Options are handled generically as feature-to-setting entries; the model will ignore options it doesn't recognize. The options could even include things like an Eclipse progress monitor...

        An implementation typically uses the URI converter of the containing model set to create an input stream, and then delegates to load(InputStream, Map).

        When the load completes, the errors and warnings can be consulted. An implementation will typically deserialize as much of a document as possible while producing diagnostics for any problems that are encountered.

        Parameters:
        options - the load options.
        Throws:
        IOException
